Tidyverse

library(tidyverse)

1 Importing Data

If we had a dataset we were working with, we would do the following:

library(readr)

dataframe <- read_csv("datasource.csv")

Since we do not have a dataset, we are going to use the gapminder data as an example.

library(gapminder)

gapminder %>%
  head()
country continent year lifeExp pop gdpPercap
Afghanistan Asia 1952 28.801 8425333 779.4453
Afghanistan Asia 1957 30.332 9240934 820.8530
Afghanistan Asia 1962 31.997 10267083 853.1007
Afghanistan Asia 1967 34.020 11537966 836.1971
Afghanistan Asia 1972 36.088 13079460 739.9811
Afghanistan Asia 1977 38.438 14880372 786.1134

2 Missing Values

2.1 Set what counts as missing

dataframe <- read_csv("datasource.csv", na = c("", "NA", "UNKNOWN","etc."))

2.2 Find/select missing values

dataframe %>%
  filter(is.na(column))

2.3 Find/select non-missing values

dataframe %>%
  filter(!is.na(column))

There are special functions that can be used within the select function:

  • starts_with(), ends_with(), contains()
  • matches()
  • num_range()
  • one_of()
  • everything()
  • “-” removed a column

3.3 Select specific values

gapminder %>%
  filter(year == 2007, country == "United States")
country continent year lifeExp pop gdpPercap
United States Americas 2007 78.242 301139947 42951.65 
gapminder %>%
  filter(year == 2007, country == "United States" | country == "Canada")
country continent year lifeExp pop gdpPercap
Canada Americas 2007 80.653 33390141 36319.24
United States Americas 2007 78.242 301139947 42951.65 
north_amer <- c("United States","Canada","Mexico")
gapminder %>%
  filter(year == 2007, country %in% north_amer)
country continent year lifeExp pop gdpPercap
Canada Americas 2007 80.653 33390141 36319.24
Mexico Americas 2007 76.195 108700891 11977.57
United States Americas 2007 78.242 301139947 42951.65

  mutate(pop = pop / 1000000) %>%
  head()

4.3 Recasting = changing the data type

4.3.1 Character to Number

dataframe %>%
  mutate(column = parse_number(column))

4.3.2 Character to Date

dataframe %>%
  mutate(column = dmy(column))

4.4 Recoding ~ find and replace

4.4.1 Characters

dateframe <- dataframe %>% 
  mutate(char_col = recode(char_col, "old" = "new")

4.4.2 Numbers

dateframe <- dataframe %>% 
  mutate(num_col = recode(num_col, `100` = 10)

4.4.3 Coding NAs

dateframe <- dataframe %>% 
  mutate(char_col = recode(char_col, "forgot" = NA_character_) %>%
  mutate(num_col = recode(num_col, "forgot" = NA_integer_)

4.4.4 Adding a default fill

dateframe <- dataframe %>% 
  mutate(column = recode(column, .default = "value")

4.5 Within-String Edits

4.5.1 Upper and lower cases

dataframe %>% 
  mutate(col = str_to_upper(col),
         col = str_to_lower(col))

4.5.2 Within-string find and replace

dataframe %>%
  mutate(col = str_replace(col,"old","new"),
         col = str_remove(col, "cut"))

4.5.3 Split into two columns

dataframe %>%
  separate(column, into = c("col1", "col2"), convert = TRUE)

4.5.4 Join into one column

dataframe %>%
  unite(new_col, col1, col2, sep = " ")

4.6 Cases

gapminder %>%
  mutate(size = case_when(
    pop > 1.959e+07 ~ "Large",
    pop < 2.794e+06 ~ "Small",
    TRUE ~ "Middle")) %>%
  filter(year==2007) %>%
  head()

joined_data <- data1 %>%

4.9 Tidy

4.9.1 Gather

dataframe %>% 
  gather(key = key_name, value = value_name, factor_key = TRUE)

4.9.2 Spread

dataframe %>% 
  spread(key = key_name, value = value_name, convert = TRUE)
